# FlowSync Architecture

## Data (`src/data/`)

- **Never** define mock arrays, config objects, stat lists, nav items, or style maps inline in components/pages.
- Put static/mock data in `src/data/` with a clear filename: `admin-organizations.ts`, `admin-nav-items.ts`, `auth-previews.ts`, etc.
- Icon maps tied to data keys may live in the same data file (see `nav-items.ts`, `admin-dashboard.ts`).

## Helpers vs utils

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/lib/helper.ts` | Reusable data/formatting helpers: `formatDate`, `formatCurrency`, `pluralize`, `paginateItems`, `matchesSearchQuery`, `normalizeEmail`, `delay` |
| `src/lib/utils.ts` | UI/DOM only: `cn`, `scrollToSection`, `isSectionActive` |

Check `helper.ts` before adding a new formatter or string/number utility.

## Routing

- Public/auth routes → `src/router/public-routes.ts`
- Admin routes → `src/router/admin-routes.ts`

## Table columns

- Define Ant Design table columns in `src/columns/`, one file per table: `organization-table-columns.tsx`
- Pages/components import columns; keep render logic out of column files where possible.

## Reusable UI (`src/component/ui/`)

- `modal.tsx` — Ant Design Modal wrapper + `ConfirmModal` for confirmations
- `table.tsx` — themed Ant Design Table + custom empty state props
- `table-empty.tsx`, `table-pagination-footer.tsx` — empty UI and footer (summary left, pagination right)

Use `ConfirmModal` for destructive actions (logout, bulk delete).

## General

- Match existing naming, Tailwind tokens, and Ant Design + ConfigProvider patterns.
- Keep diffs focused; do not refactor unrelated code.
